What do HTML and CSS stand for?
HyperText Markup Language and Cascading Style Sheets

Would you rather use HTML or CSS, for putting paragraphs of text on a webpage?
 HTML.

Would you rather use HTML or CSS, to change the font and background color of a button?
CSS but we can also change  basic font to bold with HTML also.

What is an HTML tag?
A piece of element wrapped in opening and closing tags is known as HTML tag.

What are the three parts of an HTML element? (image from paragraph)
Opening tag, content, closing tag

What is the purpose of the doctype declaration?
It is used to tell the browser what version of Html is used to render
the document <!Doctype html>.

What is the HTML element?
It is a root element,meaning that every other element will be descendant of it.

What is the purpose of the head element?
The purpose is where we put meta Information about our webpages,inside Head element
we should not use any element that displays content on the webpage.

What is the purpose of the body element?
The body element is needed to complete the HTML boiler plate,in which where all 
the content is displayed to the users.

How do you create a paragraph in HTML?
Using element  <p></p>.

How do you create a heading in HTML?
using h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6.

How many different levels of headings are there and what is the difference between them?
There are 6 levels h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6.
The difference between each heading is it has difference font sizes.

What element should you use to make text bold and important?
<strong></strong> element.

What element should you use to make text italicized to add emphasis to it?
<i></i> for italicized and <em></em> for emphasis.

What relationship does an element have with any nested elements within it?
It is their parent element.

What relationship do two elements have if they are at the same level of nesting?
The elements are siblings

How do you create HTML comments?
place a <!-- tag before and --> and after the code we create HTML comments.

What HTML tag is used to create an unordered list?
<ul></ul> 

What HTML tag is used to create an ordered list?
<ol></ol>

What HTML tag is used to create list items within both unordered and ordered lists?
<li></li> is used to display list items in which it is used 
both within unorderd and ordered lists.

What element is used to create a link?
<a href=""></a>.

What is an attribute?
Attributes are used to provide additional information about elements

What attribute tells links where to go?
href atribute.

What is the difference between an absolute and relative link?
An absolute path is a path that describes the exact location of a file or folder regardless of the current working
directory.
Relative link is a path that describes the location of a file or folder in relative to the current working directory.

Which element is used to display an image?
<image src=""></img>.

What two attributes do images always need to have?
The two attributes images have src and alt.

How do you access a parent directory in a file path?
"./"

What are the four main image formats that you can use for images on the web?
GIF, JPG, PNG and BMP.